#Approach:

Spiral Matrix – Boundary Traversal Approach

Is problem me hume matrix ko spiral order me print karna hota hai.
Iske liye hum 4 boundaries maintain karte hain:
top, bottom, left, right.

Jab tak left <= right aur top <= bottom ho,
tab tak hum spiral traversal karte rahenge.

Step 1: Top row traverse karo (left → right), phir top++
Step 2: Right column traverse karo (top → bottom), phir right--
Step 3: Bottom row traverse karo (right → left), phir bottom-- 
        (ye step tabhi karna jab top <= bottom ho)
Step 4: Left column traverse karo (bottom → top), phir left++
        (ye step tabhi karna jab left <= right ho)

Is tarah har layer ka outer boundary traverse hota hai
aur hum dheere dheere andar ki taraf badhte jaate hain.

Time Complexity: O(n * m)
Space Complexity: O(1) (excluding output list)

#Code:
class Solution {
    public List<Integer> spiralOrder(int[][] matrix) {
        int n = matrix.length;
        int m = matrix[0].length;
        int left = 0;
        int right = m-1;
        int top = 0;
        int bottom = n-1;
        List<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();

        while(left <= right && top <= bottom){
            //left
            for(int i=left; i<=right; i++){
                ans.add(matrix[top][i]);
            }
            top++;

            //right
            for(int i=top; i<=bottom; i++){
                ans.add(matrix[i][right]);
            }
            right--;

            //left
            if(top <= bottom){
                for(int i=right; i>=left; i--){
                    ans.add(matrix[bottom][i]);
                }
                bottom--;
            }

            //botom
            if(left <= right){
                for(int i=bottom; i>=top; i--){
                    ans.add(matrix[i][left]);
                }
                left++;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
